You can identify your Personal ID through the following actions:
It is indicated in Annex No. 1 of the contract, under the 'Subscriber' section;
It is indicated in the electronic invoice;
It can be identified by calling Customer Support at: 022 844 555 or 022 844 444;
It can also be identified by contacting your personal manager at the numbers indicated in the electronic invoice.

en.how_find_login_password:
How can I find my login and password for my personal account?

As a login identifier, you can use:
Personal ID – it is indicated in the contract and electronic invoice;
Login – can be identified by calling Customer Support or your personal manager;
The login password can be created through the 'Reset Password' function.

en.suspend_services:
How can I suspend services for a period of time?

Services can be suspended for a period of 7 to 120 days, based on a written request.
Holiday suspension is a service that is provided for a predetermined fee.
Holiday suspension may be restricted by the commercial offer; see the provisions of Annex No. 1 of the signed contract with StarNet.
The period of application for holiday suspension is established according to the conditions below:
From 7 to 60 days for contracts with unexpired minimum contractual terms (maximum number of cumulative suspended days for the last 12 months of active service use);
From 7 to 120 days for contracts with expired minimum contractual terms (maximum number of cumulative suspended days for the last 12 months of active service use);
The request regarding holiday service suspension can be submitted in one of the ways below:
At one of StarNet’s commercial offices;
By email at info@starnet.md;
By contacting your personal manager or Customer Support at: 022 844 444.

en.change_address_services:
How can I change the address for service provision?

The request to change the address for StarNet services can be submitted in one of the ways below:
At one of StarNet’s commercial offices;
By email at info@starnet.md;
By contacting your personal manager or Customer Support at the number: 022 844 444.

en.change_subscription:
How can I change my subscription?

You can migrate to another subscription by submitting a written request to the Provider, provided that:
There are no outstanding debts;
The difference between the contracted subscription and the requested one must be paid, if migrating to a subscription with a higher cost;
The fee for additional services for connection and/or additional equipment must be paid if the subscription you are migrating to includes such services and/or equipment;
Other conditions of the newly requested subscription must be met.
